                "title": "Improved variant discovery through local re-alignment of short-read next-generation sequencing data using SRMA", 
                "abstract": "A primary component of next-generation sequencing analysis is to align short reads to a reference genome, with each read aligned independently. However, reads that observe the same non-reference DNA sequence are highly correlated and can be used to better model the true variation in the target genome. A novel short-read micro re-aligner, SRMA, that leverages this correlation to better resolve a consensus of the underlying DNA sequence of the targeted genome is described here. Â© 2010 Homer and Nelson; licensee BioMed Central Ltd.", 
